{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014sv5JCfXXyfchPXizPdzRT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have everything needed. Let me write the plan document and save it as a ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2052,"cache_read_input_tokens":32768,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2052},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc1ffbcd-5104-4a09-8af8-b05990220769","uuid":"ba72ee8f-9da7-4080-8f59-af991fcfc631","request_id":"req_011Cc2hNeZfUpKdESjnD3jyD"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014sv5JCfXXyfchPXizPdzRT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0116ZowqbdKEBuMqZ5XgTABv","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Change / Migration Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-14  \n**Namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-change-plan-only-20260614-06403  \n**Status:** DRAFT — for review only; no changes applied\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (as-found)\n\n### 1.1 Cluster topology\n\n| Node | Role | RabbitMQ | Erlang/OTP | Maintenance |\n|------|------|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n| rabbitmq-0 | disk | 3.12.14 | 25.3.2.15 | none |\n| rabbitmq-1 | disk | 3.12.14 | 25.3.2.15 | none |\n| rabbitmq-2 | disk | 3.12.14 | 25.3.2.15 | none |\n\n- Container image: `rabbitmq:3.12-management`\n- No active alarms, no network partitions\n- All nodes running; 3-node quorum on all quorum/stream queues is achievable\n\n### 1.2 Virtual hosts\n\n| vhost | Notes |\n|-------|-------|\n| `/`   | Default vhost, no queues |\n| `/app`| Application vhost, contains active queue |\n\n### 1.3 Users and permissions\n\n| User | Tags | `/` configure/write/read | `/app` configure/write/read |\n|------|------|--------------------------|------------------------------|\n| admin    | administrator | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` |\n| app-user | (none)        | —                  | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` |\n\n`app-user` has no management-UI tags (cannot log into the HTTP API dashboard).\n\n### 1.4 Queues\n\n| vhost | Queue | Type | Durable | Arguments |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | **classic** | true | (none) |\n\nNo quorum queues, no stream queues, no HA policies.\n\n### 1.5 Policies\n\nNo policies defined on any vhost.\n\n### 1.6 Plugins enabled\n\n`rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`,\n`rabbitmq_web_dispatch`, `amqp_client`, `cowboy`, `cowlib`.\n\n### 1.7 Feature flags (all enabled)\n\n`quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`,\n`classic_queue_type_delivery_support`, `direct_exchange_routing_v2`,\n`feature_flags_v2`, `maintenance_mode_status`, `user_limits`,\n`virtual_host_metadata`, and others — all enabled.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| RabbitMQ 3.12 is **out of support** (no security patches) | HIGH | Upgrade to 3.13 → 4.x promptly |\n| `app-queue` is a **classic** durable queue with no HA | MEDIUM | Convert to quorum queue before upgrade |\n| `app-user` has full configure/write/read on `/app` (over-privileged for a typical app account) | LOW | Tighten write-only or resource-scoped permissions |\n| No policies set — no TTL, overflow, or dead-letter protections | LOW | Add policies during/after upgrade as appropriate |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Proposed Changes\n\n### 3.1 Convert `app-queue` to a quorum queue\n\nClassic queues do not support in-place conversion; migration requires:\n\n1. Create a new quorum queue named `app-queue-quorum` (or reuse the same name after\n   drain) on vhost `/app`:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl declare_queue -p /app --name app-queue-quorum --type quorum --durable\n   ```\n   Or via HTTP API:\n   ```\n   PUT /api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue-quorum\n   {\"durable\":true,\"arguments\":{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}}\n   ```\n2. Update producer/consumer bindings to target the new queue name.\n3. Drain messages from `app-queue` (let consumers process to zero depth), then delete it:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue\n   ```\n4. Optionally rename `app-queue-quorum` → `app-queue` by repeating the drain+recreate cycle,\n   if the application requires the original queue name and cannot be updated.\n\n**Do this before the RabbitMQ version upgrade** so the queue is already in quorum\nmode for the rolling restart.\n\n### 3.2 Upgrade path: 3.12 → 3.13 → 4.0 → 4.1\n\nRabbitMQ only supports single-minor-version upgrades in a rolling cluster.\nThe required sequence is:\n\n```\n3.12.14  →  3.13.x  →  4.0.x  →  4.1.x (current release series)\n```\n\nEach hop is a **rolling StatefulSet restart** (one pod at a time).\n\n#### Step A — Upgrade to 3.13.x\n\n1. Verify all feature flags are enabled (already confirmed above).\n2. Update the StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:3.13-management` (or a pinned patch\n   like `3.13.8-management`).\n3. Apply the StatefulSet change with `updateStrategy: RollingUpdate` and\n   `partition` set to 2 (upgrades rabbitmq-2 first), then 1, then 0:\n   ```\n   kubectl rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq -n <namespace>\n   ```\n   Wait for each node to become `Running` and rejoin the cluster before proceeding\n   to the next partition decrement.\n4. After all nodes are on 3.13, run:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n   to activate any new 3.13 feature flags.\n\n#### Step B — Upgrade to 4.0.x\n\nRepeat the rolling restart procedure with image `rabbitmq:4.0-management`\n(or a pinned patch). Notable 4.0 changes to be aware of:\n\n- Classic queue mirroring is **removed** in 4.0 — any remaining classic queues\n  with HA policies will fail. Confirm `app-queue` migration is complete (Step 3.1)\n  before this step.\n- Erlang/OTP minimum is raised to 26; the official `rabbitmq:4.0-management` image\n  bundles Erlang 26 — no separate action required if using the official image.\n- Run `enable_feature_flag all` after completion.\n\n#### Step C — Upgrade to 4.1.x\n\nRepeat rolling restart with image `rabbitmq:4.1-management`. Run\n`enable_feature_flag all` after completion.\n\n### 3.3 Permission tightening for `app-user` (optional but recommended)\n\n`app-user` currently has full `configure`, `write`, and `read` on `/app`.\nFor a typical application service account only publishing and consuming:\n\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"\" \"^app-.*\" \"^app-.*\"\n```\n\nThis restricts the user to write/read only on resources matching `^app-.*` and\nprevents it from declaring/deleting arbitrary exchanges or queues.\n\n### 3.4 Add baseline policies (optional)\n\nConsider adding the following policies on `/app` post-upgrade:\n\n| Policy name | Pattern | Definition | Apply-to |\n|-------------|---------|------------|----------|\n| `ha-quorum` | `.*` | `{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}` | queues (new declarations default to quorum) |\n| `ttl-default` | `.*` | `{\"message-ttl\":86400000}` | queues (24 h TTL to prevent unbounded growth) |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Pre-upgrade Checklist\n\n- [ ] Snapshot / backup mnesia data directory (or use a volume snapshot)\n- [ ] Confirm consumer applications tolerate a brief per-node restart\n- [ ] Convert `app-queue` to quorum queue and verify zero message depth before proceeding\n- [ ] Test upgraded image in a staging namespace first\n- [ ] Confirm `kubectl rollout status` returns `successfully rolled out` at each step\n- [ ] After each version hop, run `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` to verify all 3 nodes are\n      `Running` before proceeding to the next hop\n\n## 5. Rollback Notes\n\n- Rolling back a RabbitMQ **version downgrade** is not supported once the higher version\n  has written to the Mnesia database. Take a full volume snapshot before each upgrade step.\n- If a node fails mid-upgrade and cannot rejoin, remove it from the cluster\n  (`rabbitmqctl forget_cluster_node`) and reprovision from the StatefulSet.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Summary of Actions (in order)\n\n1. **Now (pre-change window):** Create `app-queue-quorum` (quorum), redirect traffic, drain and delete `app-queue` (classic).\n2. **Change window step 1:** Rolling image update `3.12-management` → `3.13-management`; enable all feature flags.\n3. **Change window step 2:** Rolling image update `3.13-management` → `4.0-management`; enable all feature flags.\n4. **Change window step 3:** Rolling image update `4.0-management` → `4.1-management`; enable all feature flags.\n5. **Post-upgrade:** Tighten `app-user` permissions; add TTL/HA policies on `/app`; update monitoring alerts for 4.x metric names.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2052,"cache_read_input_tokens":32768,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2052},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc1ffbcd-5104-4a09-8af8-b05990220769","uuid":"709fbe96-9a15-486b-b084-c569dbe9c30f","request_id":"req_011Cc2hNeZfUpKdESjnD3jyD"}
