{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PZyW9MEUt6iqLueFatBKAK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CX5JRuYvtEHpuKezKi1FhT","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/plan.md << 'PLANEOF'\n# RabbitMQ Change / Migration Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-14  \n**Namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-change-plan-only-20260614-06403  \n**Status:** DRAFT — for review only; no changes applied\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (as-found)\n\n### 1.1 Cluster topology\n\n| Node | Role | RabbitMQ | Erlang/OTP | Maintenance |\n|------|------|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n| rabbitmq-0 | disk | 3.12.14 | 25.3.2.15 | none |\n| rabbitmq-1 | disk | 3.12.14 | 25.3.2.15 | none |\n| rabbitmq-2 | disk | 3.12.14 | 25.3.2.15 | none |\n\n- Container image: `rabbitmq:3.12-management`\n- No active alarms, no network partitions\n- All nodes running; 3-node quorum on quorum/stream queues is achievable\n\n### 1.2 Virtual hosts\n\n| vhost | Notes |\n|-------|-------|\n| `/`   | Default vhost, no queues |\n| `/app`| Application vhost, contains active queue |\n\n### 1.3 Users and permissions\n\n| User | Tags | `/` configure/write/read | `/app` configure/write/read |\n|------|------|--------------------------|------------------------------|\n| admin    | administrator | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` |\n| app-user | (none)        | —                  | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` |\n\n`app-user` has no management-UI tags (cannot log into the HTTP API dashboard).\n\n### 1.4 Queues\n\n| vhost | Queue | Type | Durable | Arguments |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | **classic** | true | (none) |\n\nNo quorum queues, no stream queues, no HA policies.\n\n### 1.5 Policies\n\nNo policies defined on any vhost.\n\n### 1.6 Plugins enabled\n\n`rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`,\n`rabbitmq_web_dispatch`, `amqp_client`, `cowboy`, `cowlib`.\n\n### 1.7 Feature flags (all enabled)\n\n`quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`,\n`classic_queue_type_delivery_support`, `direct_exchange_routing_v2`,\n`feature_flags_v2`, `maintenance_mode_status`, `user_limits`,\n`virtual_host_metadata`, and others — all enabled.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| RabbitMQ 3.12 is **out of support** (no security patches) | HIGH | Upgrade to 3.13 then 4.x promptly |\n| `app-queue` is a **classic** durable queue with no HA | MEDIUM | Convert to quorum queue before upgrade |\n| `app-user` has full configure/write/read on `/app` (over-privileged for a typical app account) | LOW | Tighten to write+read only on matching resources |\n| No policies set — no TTL, overflow, or dead-letter protections | LOW | Add policies during/after upgrade as appropriate |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Proposed Changes\n\n### 3.1 Convert `app-queue` to a quorum queue\n\nClassic queues do not support in-place conversion; migration requires:\n\n1. Create a new quorum queue named `app-queue-quorum` on vhost `/app`:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl declare_queue -p /app --name app-queue-quorum --type quorum --durable\n   ```\n   Or via HTTP API:\n   ```\n   PUT /api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue-quorum\n   {\"durable\":true,\"arguments\":{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}}\n   ```\n2. Update producer/consumer bindings to target the new queue name.\n3. Drain messages from `app-queue` (let consumers process to zero depth), then delete it:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue\n   ```\n4. Optionally rename `app-queue-quorum` back to `app-queue` (drain+recreate cycle) if\n   the application cannot be updated to use the new name.\n\n**Perform this before the RabbitMQ version upgrade** so the queue is already in quorum\nmode for the rolling restart.\n\n### 3.2 Upgrade path: 3.12 → 3.13 → 4.0 → 4.1\n\nRabbitMQ only supports single-minor-version upgrades in a rolling cluster.\nThe required sequence is:\n\n```\n3.12.14  →  3.13.x  →  4.0.x  →  4.1.x (current supported series)\n```\n\nEach hop is a **rolling StatefulSet restart** (one pod at a time).\n\n#### Step A — Upgrade to 3.13.x\n\n1. Verify all feature flags are enabled (already confirmed above).\n2. Update the StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:3.13-management` (or a pinned patch such as\n   `rabbitmq:3.13.8-management`).\n3. Apply the change with `updateStrategy: RollingUpdate`; use `partition` to control order\n   (start with rabbitmq-2, then 1, then 0):\n   ```\n   kubectl rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq -n <namespace>\n   ```\n   Wait for each node to show `Running` and rejoin the cluster before moving to the next pod.\n4. After all nodes are on 3.13, run:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n\n#### Step B — Upgrade to 4.0.x\n\nRepeat the rolling restart with image `rabbitmq:4.0-management`. Key 4.0 changes:\n\n- Classic queue **mirroring is removed** in 4.0. Any remaining classic queues with HA\n  policies will not start. Ensure Step 3.1 is complete before this step.\n- Erlang/OTP minimum raised to 26; the official image bundles Erlang 26 — no separate action\n  needed when using the official image.\n- Run `enable_feature_flag all` after all nodes are updated.\n\n#### Step C — Upgrade to 4.1.x\n\nRepeat rolling restart with image `rabbitmq:4.1-management`. Run\n`enable_feature_flag all` after completion.\n\n### 3.3 Permission tightening for `app-user` (recommended)\n\n`app-user` currently has full `configure`, `write`, and `read` on `/app`. For a\ntypical application service account (publish + consume only):\n\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"\" \"^app-.*\" \"^app-.*\"\n```\n\nThis prevents the app account from declaring or deleting arbitrary exchanges/queues,\nrestricting it to resources matching the `app-` prefix.\n\n### 3.4 Add baseline policies (recommended post-upgrade)\n\nConsider adding the following policies on `/app` after the upgrade is complete:\n\n| Policy name | Pattern | Definition | Apply-to |\n|-------------|---------|------------|----------|\n| `ttl-default` | `.*` | `{\"message-ttl\":86400000}` | queues (24 h TTL to prevent unbounded growth) |\n| `overflow-reject` | `.*` | `{\"overflow\":\"reject-publish\"}` | queues (back-pressure instead of silent drop) |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Pre-upgrade Checklist\n\n- [ ] Take volume snapshot of PVCs backing rabbitmq-0/1/2 (Mnesia data)\n- [ ] Confirm consumer applications tolerate a brief per-node restart (≤30 s)\n- [ ] Convert `app-queue` to quorum queue; verify zero message depth before proceeding\n- [ ] Test upgraded image in a staging namespace first\n- [ ] After each rolling restart, run `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` to confirm all 3 nodes\n      are in Running state before proceeding to the next version hop\n- [ ] Confirm `kubectl rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq` returns `successfully rolled out`\n      at each step\n\n## 5. Rollback Notes\n\n- RabbitMQ **does not support version downgrades** once the higher version has written to\n  Mnesia. Volume snapshots before each step are the only reliable rollback path.\n- If a node fails mid-upgrade and cannot rejoin the cluster, remove it with\n  `rabbitmqctl forget_cluster_node <node>` and reprovision from the StatefulSet.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Summary of Actions (in order)\n\n1. **Pre-change window:** Create `app-queue-quorum` (quorum type), redirect traffic,\n   drain and delete `app-queue` (classic).\n2. **Change window step 1:** Rolling image update `3.12-management` → `3.13-management`;\n   enable all feature flags.\n3. **Change window step 2:** Rolling image update `3.13-management` → `4.0-management`;\n   enable all feature flags.\n4. **Change window step 3:** Rolling image update `4.0-management` → `4.1-management`;\n   enable all feature flags.\n5. **Post-upgrade:** Tighten `app-user` permissions; add TTL/overflow policies on `/app`;\n   update monitoring dashboards for any 4.x metric name changes.\nPLANEOF\necho \"Written.\"","description":"Write the migration plan to /tmp/plan.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3249,"cache_read_input_tokens":34820,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3249},"output_tokens":43,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc1ffbcd-5104-4a09-8af8-b05990220769","uuid":"2b74b540-b18d-42ad-b75e-de4672d1c17a","request_id":"req_011Cc2hSe8jCFCpbwcfS6buK"}
